Add a serialisation and deep-object utilities module. Create `src/serializer.js` with the following:

1) `deepClone(value)` - returns a deep clone of any JSON-serialisable value (handles objects, arrays, primitives, Date, null, undefined).

2) `deepEqual(a, b)` - returns true if two values are deeply equal. Handles objects, arrays, Date, null, undefined, and primitive types. Does NOT rely on JSON.stringify (must handle object key order differences).

3) `deepMerge(...sources)` - deeply merges multiple objects together into a new object. Arrays from later sources replace (not concat) arrays from earlier ones. Primitive values from later sources override earlier ones.

4) `flatten(obj, delimiter?, prefix?)` - flattens a nested object to a single-depth object with delimited keys (default delimiter '.'). E.g. `{ a: { b: 1 } }` becomes `{ 'a.b': 1 }`. Handles arrays (keys like 'arr.0', 'arr.1').

5) `unflatten(obj, delimiter?)` - reverses `flatten`. Reconstructs a nested object from delimited keys.

6) `pick(obj, keys)` - returns a shallow object with only the specified keys.

7) `omit(obj, keys)` - returns a shallow object without the specified keys.

8) `mapValues(obj, fn)` - returns a new object with each value mapped through `fn(value, key)`.

9) `mapKeys(obj, fn)` - returns a new object with each key transformed by `fn(key, value)`.

10) `groupBy(array, keyFn)` - groups an array of items into an object by the result of `keyFn(item)`.

11) Write tests in `tests/serializer.test.js` for all functions covering edge cases (circular-safe deepEqual returning false, empty objects/arrays, nested structures, date equality).

12) Export all functions from `src/index.js` as `serializer`.
